---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Aside from '../../../components/Aside.astro';
import { streamsSidebar } from '../../../data/streams-sidebar';
import { Code } from 'astro:components';
---

<DocsLayout title="Extending Streams" sidebar={streamsSidebar} description="Custom operators, Flow interop, and platform summary">

<h1>Extending Streams</h1>

<p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
  Build your own operators, bridge to Kotlin Flow, and understand the platform matrix.
</p>

<h2>Custom operators</h2>

<p>Build operators by extending <code>StreamMapper</code> (transform) or <code>StreamWrapper</code> (pass-through):</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.streams.Stream
import io.peekandpoke.ultra.streams.StreamMapper

fun Stream<Int>.clamp(min: Int, max: Int): Stream<Int> =
    StreamMapper(
        wrapped = this,
        mapper = { it.coerceIn(min, max) }
    )

val source = StreamSource(50)
val clamped = source.clamp(0, 100)

source(150)
println(clamped())  // 100`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<p>For operators with internal state, extend <code>StreamWrapperBase</code> directly and override <code>handleIncoming()</code> and <code>invoke()</code>.</p>

<h2>Flow interop</h2>

<p>Convert any stream to a Kotlin <code>Flow</code>:</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.streams.ops.asFlow

val source = StreamSource(1)

source.asFlow()
    .filter { it > 5 }
    .take(3)
    .collect { println(it) }`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<p>The Flow emits the current value immediately on collection, then subsequent values. Cancelling the collector unsubscribes automatically.</p>

    <Aside>We didn't try to replace Flow. Sometimes you need the full coroutines ecosystem. This bridge lets you get
        there without rewriting everything.
    </Aside>

    <h2>Platform summary</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-8">
  <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
    <thead>
      <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
        <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Operator</th>
        <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Platform</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="text-gray-400">
      <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
        <td class="py-2">map, filter, combine, fold, distinct, fallback, history, indexed, onEach, cutoff</td>
        <td class="py-2">All platforms</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
        <td class="py-2">ticker, debounce, mapAsync, asFlow</td>
        <td class="py-2">All platforms (coroutine-based)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
        <td class="py-2"><code>animTicker()</code></td>
        <td class="py-2">JS only (<code>requestAnimationFrame</code>)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
        <td class="py-2"><code>persistInLocalStorage()</code></td>
        <td class="py-2">JS only (<code>localStorage</code>)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="py-2"><code>debouncedFunc()</code>, <code>debouncedFuncExceptFirst()</code></td>
        <td class="py-2">JS only (<code>setTimeout</code>)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

</DocsLayout>
